# Skill: Service Generation (Frontend)

## Goal
Create or update a service module in `src/services/<domain>/` that follows project boundaries.

## Required Structure
- Service implementation: `src/services/<domain>/index.ts`
- Service types: `src/services/<domain>/types.ts` (or `src/services/types.ts` for shared types)
- HTTP calls must use `src/services/api-client.ts`
- Storage dependencies must come from `src/storage/*`

## Rules
- Do not import UI/components/routes in services.
- Keep services framework-agnostic and side-effect-light.
- Normalize API errors through existing API error helpers.
- Export typed functions; avoid `any`.

## Checklist
- [ ] Domain folder exists in `src/services/`
- [ ] Uses `apiClient`
- [ ] Uses existing storage wrapper if tokens/session are required
- [ ] Types are defined and exported
- [ ] No feature/page/component imports
